  "why": "The paper designs and evaluates a testing framework, DeepCruiser, for stateful deep learning systems, with a focus on Automated Speech Recognition (ASR). The oracle used to identify failures is based on transcription accuracy. A test case is considered a failure if the Word/Character Error Rate (W/CER) of the model's output exceeds a predefined threshold. The evaluation exclusively uses W/CER to quantify the 'erroneous degree' of the model's predictions. This type of failure—incorrect transcription—is a form of misprediction or accuracy degradation, which falls under the category of 'robustness-related failures'. The paper does not demonstrate testing against a model with explicit safety or security safeguards, nor does it show that the discovered mispredictions lead to harmful, unsafe, or biased behavior.",
